        {
          "username": "sarcastic ramen",
          "rating": 1,
          "contributor_id": "118376563580637773998",
          "user_review_count": 1,
          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWrh20TM5NVVSeb9HkWFgG2b6wqAXqSwXOfoOfA-2bnegUJHX4lLg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "I scheduled an urgent care appointment online for a physical exam for my job and I provided my insurance and personal information in advance. The system indicated that the appointment would have no cost. I arrived slightly late and called the office to inform them. During the call, I was told that I could not be seen because the type of appointment scheduled online was listed as a physical and the office doesn\u2019t provide physicals after 8. So how come I was able to make an appointment through their system? During the conversation, the staff member I spoke with on the phone abruptly hung up on me.\n\nWhen I attempted to address the situation upon arrival , I was told that the office did not even have my basic information on file and that there would be a $150 cost, which contradicted what I had been quoted when booking the appointment online.\n\nThe staff member who assisted me was extremely hostile and unprofessional. She spoke to me with a dismissive and rude attitude and ultimately told me that I needed to leave without making any attempt to clarify the situation or assist me. I did not receive her name, but she appeared to be a young, slender woman with tan skin, curly hair, and glasses who was working around 7:00 PM on March 12.\n\nOverall, this was one of the most unprofessional clinical experiences I have had. I am very disappointed with how the situation was handled and with the lack of basic customer service and professionalism. I understand that insurance costs vary, but I did not appreciate the way the situation was handled and how I was spoken to.\n\n(P.S it does look like this place has a lot of bad reviews and the response is to just copy and paste the same generic \u201capology\u201d. What a horrible location)",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xkZlQxTmxXRlJQWjBacmVVbGpjR2d6Ukhka2QyYxAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x50a9d141bee8c2ea!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOldfT1NlWFRPZ0ZreUljcGgzRHdkd2c%7C%7C?hl=en",
